Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.63,0:00:07.19,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,One human only has the power to do so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.03,0:00:25.54,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm going to protect...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.54,0:00:28.13,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,...even if it's just a handful of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.92,0:00:31.01,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,...the ones most important to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.65,0:00:37.39,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,A subordinate protects their subordinate, and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.65,0:00:41.07,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,That should be possible, even for us puny humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.07,0:00:42.39,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Geometric progression?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.15,0:00:45.27,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Which means this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.16,0:00:48.56,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to protect this whole country,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.56,0:00:51.23,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,you have to be at the top of the summit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.67,0:00:57.08,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,It must feel great up there, Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.20,0:01:02.24,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't climb to the top with my own strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.19,0:01:05.02,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.02,0:01:07.37,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,What are you getting all worked up for?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.25,0:01:10.87,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.87,0:01:12.85,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.85,0:01:17.43,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I want to see what kind of changes\Nyour naive ideals will bring to this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.69,0:01:24.39,Default,Haw,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.29,0:01:26.14,Default,Haw,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.69,0:01:31.59,Default,Haw,0000,0000,0000,,Why not head to the nap room if you're tired?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.59,0:01:33.93,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.59,0:01:39.34,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to finish up the documents I've started before I get transferred to Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.86,0:01:42.11,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't slept much lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.11,0:01:44.33,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,It seemed you were dreaming about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.46,0:01:48.43,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What? Just a boring flashback.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.27,0:03:25.60,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember anything after being kicked by this guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.26,0:03:31.37,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,"Guardians with only souls",\N"precious sacrifices", "being kept alive".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.96,0:03:35.93,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,"Tattoo of Ouroboros", and\N"transmutation circle for a philosopher's stone".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.93,0:03:39.86,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,According to Dr. Marcoh,\Nthe stones were used in Ishbal, as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.52,0:03:44.05,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,There are too many mysteries for it to be an ordinary experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.05,0:03:49.08,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to look into it some more,\Nbut the research lab is in ruins now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.08,0:03:51.08,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.19,0:03:55.71,Default,Brosh,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like they're discussing something tricky...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.71,0:04:00.13,Default,Ross,0000,0000,0000,,I don't feel like getting involved in something dangerous again, so I refuse to listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.52,0:04:01.88,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you two...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.78,0:04:06.81,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the Fullmetal Alchemist's recovery room?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.81,0:04:08.34,Default,Ross,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he's in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.92,0:04:14.89,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,We may be able to discover something if we look through the court-martial chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.45,0:04:21.88,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go and investigate the ones who were participating in the research of the stones under Dr. Marcoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.51,0:04:26.90,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to intrude.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.04,0:04:34.01,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,F-Führer-President... King Bradley!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.01,0:04:37.03,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet down. You can be at ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.53,0:04:40.17,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Your Excellency, may I ask why you are here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.43,0:04:41.85,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Why I'm here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.37,0:04:43.59,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,To visit this boy, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.59,0:04:45.25,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Are you fond of melon at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.25,0:04:46.74,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.40,0:04:48.55,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, something's wrong here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.50,0:04:54.29,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like you've been doing a lot of investigating of the military leadership, Major Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.29,0:04:57.30,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! Well... that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.30,0:04:58.86,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,How did you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.86,0:05:01.11,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Don't underestimate my intelligence network.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.15,0:05:05.32,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,And you, Edward Elric...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.31,0:05:08.17,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,The philosopher's stone, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.08,0:05:14.04,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Just how much did you find out?\NDepending on that, I may have to...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.22,0:05:25.17,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I'm joking!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.80,0:05:27.59,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,No need to get tense.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.79,0:05:28.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.77,0:05:34.05,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I, too, was aware there have been\Ndisquieting activities within the military.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.05,0:05:37.04,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I've always wanted to do something about them, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.04,0:05:38.95,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.95,0:05:42.40,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,A list of people who were researching the philosopher's stones, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.08,0:05:46.71,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Every one of them has been reported missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.71,0:05:47.28,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.80,0:05:51.55,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,They have been reported missing a few days prior to the destruction of Research Laboratory 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.55,0:05:54.46,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy is always ahead of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.46,0:05:59.25,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Even with my intelligence network,\Nwe still don't know the scale of it all,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.25,0:06:04.05,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,their objectives, or how close they are to achieving them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.90,0:06:08.71,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,So you're saying it's extremely dangerous for us to look into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.71,0:06:09.83,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.25,0:06:11.70,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Colonel Hughes,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.70,0:06:13.60,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Major Armstrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.60,0:06:15.29,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Elric Brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.29,0:06:18.69,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I've decided you all are trustworthy people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.60,0:06:24.44,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I forbid you to continue investigating this matter or to disclose it to others!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.36,0:06:30.70,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,You cannot trust anyone in a situation like this,\Nwhen you cannot even distinguish friend from foe!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.81,0:06:35.69,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Regard all of the military as your foe and proceed carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.12,0:06:37.22,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.38,0:06:42.12,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,When the time comes, I will have many tasks for all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.12,0:06:43.29,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,So be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.29,0:06:44.37,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.10,0:06:46.18,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Your Excellency!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.18,0:06:48.35,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,Where have you gone, Your Excellency?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.35,0:06:51.93,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, drats! Here comes my annoying subordinate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.35,0:06:56.92,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I snuck out of my office, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.42,0:06:58.88,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Farewell!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.46,0:07:05.66,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.66,0:07:06.23,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.52,0:07:09.58,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What are you guys doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.58,0:07:13.16,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just say... a storm just went by.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.70,0:07:18.28,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I went out and bought the tickets you asked for.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.28,0:07:20.41,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow's afternoon train, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.72,0:07:22.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.75,0:07:27.20,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you in such a rush?\NYour wounds haven't even healed yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.20,0:07:30.80,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stay in a place reeking of antiseptics like this forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.52,0:07:33.20,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.93,0:07:34.80,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Dublith?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.80,0:07:36.03,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.53,0:07:40.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,After discussing it with Al, we decided to stop by our master's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.80,0:07:44.60,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared, Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.96,0:07:47.66,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We're probably going to get killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.66,0:07:49.53,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,C-Courage, my little brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.53,0:07:51.28,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just as scared as you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.64,0:07:53.82,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of person is your master...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.38,0:07:57.94,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Dublith is quite far from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.94,0:07:59.24,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.24,0:08:03.00,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... It's here. It's right in the middle of the South.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.32,0:08:09.63,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.88,0:08:12.51,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,This place! Before Dublith!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.84,0:08:16.72,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,The Holy Land of Automails, Rush Valley!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.72,0:08:18.51,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I've always wanted to go there!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.67,0:08:20.14,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Please take me! Please take me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.14,0:08:21.92,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Take me! You better take me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.92,0:08:23.77,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you go by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.77,0:08:26.02,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Who's going to pay for the trip, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.02,0:08:27.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You're planning on making {\i1}me{\i0\fscx30} {\r} pay for it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.72,0:08:30.28,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, why not? It's on the way, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.87,0:08:32.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.36,0:08:33.90,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Hooray!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.82,0:08:37.66,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to give Granny a call!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.57,0:08:43.05,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, she'll make a grand wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.05,0:08:44.55,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell {\i1}me{\i0\fscx30} {\r} that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.55,0:08:47.93,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Not as grand as my wife, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.29,0:08:51.84,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Papa's going to be on his way!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.84,0:08:54.97,Default,Elicia,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to come home early today, Papa?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.97,0:08:57.45,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm, I wonder?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.45,0:08:59.47,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Papa's got a lot of work to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.77,0:09:02.47,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll come home as soon as I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.09,0:09:06.35,Default,Gracia,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to be late.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.84,0:09:10.52,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to be leaving today, right, Winry?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.52,0:09:12.70,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I can't see you off because of work, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.11,0:09:14.15,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.24,0:09:18.57,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I'm truly indebted to you, Mr. Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.33,0:09:22.86,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Be sure to drop by if you ever come to Central again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.41,0:09:25.28,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Think of it as your home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.28,0:09:28.04,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,And give my regards to those boys, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.04,0:09:28.71,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.71,0:09:31.19,Default,Elicia,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck at work, Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.19,0:09:32.59,Default,Gracia,0000,0000,0000,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.88,0:09:46.27,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you decide to go visit your master all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.27,0:09:47.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Two reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.52,0:09:51.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,First off, we've kind of been on a losing streak.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.54,0:09:52.43,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.43,0:09:54.49,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You're going because you want to get stronger?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.49,0:09:55.86,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What are you guys, muscleheads?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.35,0:09:59.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot! It's not that simple!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.72,0:10:03.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We don't just want to get stronger physically, but should we say mentally, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.43,0:10:03.99,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.31,0:10:05.65,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.65,0:10:09.75,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, we feel like we'll be able to get stronger if we visit our master.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.41,0:10:12.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I want to become far stronger than I am now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.50,0:10:17.38,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,And your second reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.65,0:10:21.51,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I want to ask about philosopher's stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.76,0:10:24.87,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,The real truth that is beyond truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.87,0:10:27.59,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We never found out the meaning of those words, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.59,0:10:30.40,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Our master might know something about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.75,0:10:33.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We can't be caring about how we're going to look out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.15,0:10:37.18,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to ask our master while being prepared to be killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.25,0:10:39.29,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.19,0:10:41.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.28,0:10:45.00,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It was a short-lived life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.00,0:10:48.38,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could have had a girlfriend, at least...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.38,0:10:50.54,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of person is your master?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.16,0:10:53.67,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,A riot in Lior?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.67,0:10:54.58,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.01,0:11:01.28,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, the riot caused by some Leto cult\Ndeceiving the citizens has finally calmed down.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.78,0:11:02.55,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.35,0:11:06.68,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,With Ishbal and other riots...\Nthe East sure have their hands full.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.35,0:11:12.15,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,Not just the East, but there are riots and border wars\Nsparking up in the North and the West.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.84,0:11:15.63,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Mountains of corpses everywhere, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.63,0:11:17.84,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,We may even get a coup soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.90,0:11:26.28,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you headed, Lt. Colonel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.79,0:11:27.98,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,To the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.31,0:11:36.08,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Riots throughout Lior.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.74,0:11:39.80,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,The ingredients of philosopher's stones are humans...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.74,0:11:43.30,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,What we did in Ishbal...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.34,0:11:49.68,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa now, who's the mastermind behind all of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.68,0:11:51.98,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I've got to hurry and let the Führer-President know...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.08,0:11:58.16,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you, Lt. Colonel Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.16,0:12:02.32,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Or should I say... farewell?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.44,0:12:18.09,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Cool tattoo you've got there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.66,0:12:21.51,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,You found out too much, Lt. Colonel Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.16,0:12:39.27,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.38,0:12:49.24,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,That's something {\i1}I{\i0\fscx30} {\r} should be saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.55,0:12:54.33,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Lt. Colonel Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.33,0:12:56.71,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,If you're here to call someone about your family again-
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.71,0:12:58.46,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Colonel, you're bleeding!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.46,0:13:01.55,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing. I need to use the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.88,0:13:04.63,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I need to call the Führer-President building...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.44,0:13:14.69,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to bother you...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.25,0:13:16.12,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Colonel!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.43,0:13:18.95,Default,Call,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? You've reached Eastern Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.95,0:13:21.86,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Let me talk to Roy... Colonel Roy Mustang.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.17,0:13:24.95,Default,Call,0000,0000,0000,,We're not permitted to relay direct calls from an outside line.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.95,0:13:27.03,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Lt. Colonel Hughes from Central!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.03,0:13:28.91,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I'm calling from a phone booth because of an emergency!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.91,0:13:30.18,Default,Call,0000,0000,0000,,Please give me the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.18,0:13:32.20,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,What a bother!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.38,0:13:38.34,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle-Sugar-Oliver-Eight-Zero-Zero!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.45,0:13:40.86,Default,Call,0000,0000,0000,,I've verified the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.86,0:13:42.31,Default,Call,0000,0000,0000,,One moment, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.31,0:13:43.54,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.54,0:13:44.80,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,The military is in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.29,0:13:53.28,Default,Ross,0000,0000,0000,,Could you put down the receiver, Lt. Colonel?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.27,0:13:57.02,Default,Ross,0000,0000,0000,,The receiver, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.18,0:14:01.37,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,2nd Lt. Ross... or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.37,0:14:02.40,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.34,0:14:06.29,Default,Ross,0000,0000,0000,,I'm 2nd Lt. Maria Ross. Have you forgotten?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.29,0:14:07.41,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,No, you're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.51,0:14:12.40,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,2nd Lt. Ross has a mole under her left eye!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.60,0:14:15.68,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.68,0:14:17.56,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,I was careless.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.50,0:14:21.54,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,How's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.25,0:14:24.80,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.80,0:14:26.82,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,It's as if I'm dreaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.22,0:14:32.18,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Your quick-wittedness brought the end of you, Lt. Colonel Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.46,0:14:34.57,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now, give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.01,0:14:37.60,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a wife and a daughter waiting for me at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.60,0:14:39.44,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.63,0:14:41.56,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,...I can die here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.99,0:14:46.40,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect staging, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.87,0:14:49.11,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.22,0:15:00.63,Default,Call,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Colonel Hughes from Central is on a public line.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.63,0:15:01.93,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.93,0:15:03.31,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Put him through.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.31,0:15:04.52,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.52,0:15:05.84,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,If it's about your daughter again, I'm hanging up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.68,0:15:10.22,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Hughes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.42,0:15:12.73,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Hughes...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.73,0:15:14.05,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Hughes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.67,0:15:24.40,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Humans are so foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.40,0:15:26.82,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Risking their lives for something so stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.60,0:15:37.78,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Elicia... Gracia...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.49,0:15:39.64,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.51,0:15:45.34,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think I can... keep my promise...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.56,0:15:54.22,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, this is delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.81,0:15:57.10,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,These apple pies are awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.10,0:16:00.46,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Gracia is such a good cook!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.46,0:16:01.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.88,0:16:04.98,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The quiche she made for us once was really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.28,0:16:10.42,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,It's on my "list of things to eat when I get my body back".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.42,0:16:14.79,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,She taught me how to make it, so I'll bake one for you when you get your body back, Al.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.79,0:16:16.37,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.78,0:16:21.25,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Hughes and Miss Gracia are both wonderful people.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.25,0:16:27.26,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Colonel Hughes is such a doting father...\Nand kind of annoying because he's so meddlesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.26,0:16:30.76,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,He always came to poke fun at you in your hospital room, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.97,0:16:32.41,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.06,0:16:39.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He's always saying he's busy with work, yet he paid me a visit every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.64,0:16:42.44,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We have to thank him next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.44,0:16:43.52,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.34,0:17:19.85,Default,Elicia,0000,0000,0000,,Mama... why are they burying Papa?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.27,0:17:22.33,Default,Gracia,0000,0000,0000,,Elicia...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.33,0:17:26.42,Default,Elicia,0000,0000,0000,,Papa won't be able to go to work if they do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.03,0:17:27.96,Default,Gracia,0000,0000,0000,,Elici...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.81,0:17:33.25,Default,Elicia,0000,0000,0000,,Papa said he had a lot of work to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.32,0:17:35.49,Default,Elicia,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.91,0:17:37.72,Default,Elicia,0000,0000,0000,,Don't bury him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.32,0:17:39.85,Default,Elicia,0000,0000,0000,,Papa!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.25,0:17:45.67,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Specially promoted two ranks after being killed in the line of duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.67,0:17:47.83,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Brigadier General Hughes... huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.30,0:17:52.54,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You said you were going to work under me and support me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.08,0:17:54.46,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What's the point if you surpass my rank?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.00,0:17:57.11,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.68,0:17:58.34,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.58,0:18:06.73,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemists are unpleasant creatures, aren't they, Lieutenant?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.98,0:18:14.00,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm desperately putting together the theory of human transmutation in my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.22,0:18:20.62,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I know how those boys felt when they tried to transmute their mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.10,0:18:25.12,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.99,0:18:28.00,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.52,0:18:32.00,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, it looks like it's beginning to rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.44,0:18:35.83,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't think so...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.78,0:18:40.77,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's raining all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.67,0:18:44.95,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.63,0:18:46.75,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.17,0:18:49.04,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,We'll catch colds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.75,0:18:54.07,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,He left the room saying that\Nhe was going to go to the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.82,0:18:57.57,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,That was the last I saw of the Lt. Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.88,0:19:01.92,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Did he fight with someone in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.92,0:19:03.22,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.70,0:19:07.32,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,There were bloodstains from the room to the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.21,0:19:10.25,Default,Fock,0000,0000,0000,,And his next destination was...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.48,0:19:15.38,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Colonel tried to make a phone call,\Neven while he was injured...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.38,0:19:19.88,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,But... he left without doing so.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.77,0:19:25.45,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,He realized something in the court-martial chamber...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.45,0:19:31.14,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,...and took the trouble to contact me from the outside when he could have called from within the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.19,0:19:37.17,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,The telephone operator in the Eastern Headquarters heard Hughes say, "The military is in danger".
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.37,0:19:39.28,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.00,0:19:42.00,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What was he trying to tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.58,0:19:48.97,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel, I've brought Major Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.02,0:19:56.86,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,We have an idea of the ones who murdered Lt. Colonel Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.86,0:19:58.80,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Then why don't you take them into custody?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.80,0:20:03.18,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,We have an idea, but we don't know exactly who they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.96,0:20:07.18,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean? Tell me in detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.39,0:20:09.18,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.48,0:20:12.53,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I, a Colonel, am telling you to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.53,0:20:14.06,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to disobey a senior officer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.08,0:20:16.06,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.44,0:20:22.68,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.68,0:20:24.52,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for calling you out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.52,0:20:25.66,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You may go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.66,0:20:26.54,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.83,0:20:34.33,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, I forgot to mention.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.33,0:20:38.21,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,The Elric Brothers had been staying here until a few days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.08,0:20:40.46,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,The Elric Brothers?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.46,0:20:42.84,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the Elric Brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.97,0:20:47.22,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Did they find what they were looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.40,0:20:48.44,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.44,0:20:51.72,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,What they are looking for is almost legendary.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.45,0:20:54.60,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.47,0:21:00.32,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,We couldn't get much out of him, could we?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.32,0:21:02.11,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.11,0:21:03.84,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,The Major is truly good-natured.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.76,0:21:07.69,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,He said specifically,\N"ones who murdered Lt. Colonel Hughes".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.69,0:21:10.58,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Which means there were several.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.58,0:21:13.62,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,It could be that they're working as an organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.89,0:21:18.84,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,If he can't speak, even under order from a colonel,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.84,0:21:24.01,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,that means someone higher ranked than me is imposing silence on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.63,0:21:27.01,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,We can assume the top of the military is behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.98,0:21:31.01,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,And the thing the Elric Brothers are looking for...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.81,0:21:33.89,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the philosopher's stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.54,0:21:41.06,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,An organization that has a hand in the military leadership, the philosopher's stone, and Lt. Colonel Hughes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.06,0:21:42.94,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Just how does it all relate...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.94,0:21:44.55,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,As for now, we don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.32,0:21:52.66,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,But once I get transferred to Central, I'll investigate the leadership and find out who killed Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.18,0:21:56.25,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,It's unlike you to mix up private and public matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.25,0:21:58.29,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,There are no "private" or "public" matters involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.29,0:22:02.65,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Aiming to become Führer-President and avenging Hughes' death...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.15,0:22:05.05,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,...are both my will as an individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.00,0:22:08.55,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Our target will be the military leadership. You're coming with me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.43,0:22:10.81,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Like I'll back down now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.73,0:24:04.42,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Ed and Al run through Rush Valley, chasing after Paninya, a girl who stole Ed's silver pocket watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.67,0:24:09.70,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,although they have no idea what's awaiting them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.94,0:24:15.43,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.43,0:24:19.43,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 11, The Miracle at Rush Valley.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.89,0:24:23.35,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,The words the boy engraved were words of resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.57,0:24:24.59,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Or could they be...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.59,0:24:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
